commentary: Amir Hamza to Sikandar Raza, no run is this a dead ball? I definitely saw a signal from the umpire, but Raza just pulled away as it was bowled, and then still played a shot to defend to cover. I'm not sure what the problem was. Raza is gesturing to his ear. Was someone talking to him from behind the stumps? In the end, it's called a live ball and they get on with it.

commentary: Mohammad Nabi to Sikandar Raza, OUT a needless run out! Raza tapped the ball just wide of mid on, but called immediately for the single. He was running to the danger end, so it was his call. Chigumbura must have heard the call, but he turned around and watched the ball instead of running. By the time he eventually set off, with Raza shouting for the single again, the ball was already being thrown to Shahzad. Ball-watching results in a run out.

commentary: Chisoro to Noor Ali Zadran, OUT gone! Noor Ali responds with an aggressive swipe outside off, but he's cut the ball in the air and straight to Chigumbura in the covers. commentary: Jongwe to Mohammad Nabi, OUT there's a collision between the fielders, but Nabi is caught! He wanted to send this over the infield, with both mid on and mid off up, but top edged the stroke. Both Panyangara, at mid on, and Masakadza, at midwicket, wanted it. Masakadza set himself under the ball, and held the catch even as Panyangara bumped into him, knocking him over. But he shows good commitment to hold on, and Zimbabwe break through again. Is it too late?

commentary:
Chisoro to Mohammad Shahzad, OUT great catch. The fielder had to run back from midwicket, dive and catch it over his shoulder. Guess who? It's Sikandar Raza, and he shows no tiredness in his legs as he leaps in the air and flings the ball up in celebration. The shot was on for Shahzad, as there was no one on the boundary, but his stroke was top edged.
Is this an opening for Zimbabwe?
